data.content:
Create `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace root with this content:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "MyMcpServer": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--project", "src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj"]
    }
  }
}
```

Then in VS Code:

1. Open **Copilot Chat** → switch to **Agent** mode
2. Click the **wrench icon** (Select Tools) → verify your server and tools appear
3. Ask a question that triggers your tool — approve execution when prompted

**If tools don't appear**, rebuild (`dotnet build`) and restart the MCP server. Also verify your tool classes have `[McpServerToolType]` and methods have `[McpServerTool]`.
